inn1.comm: starts back of a length outside off, no great carry through Buttler
short of a length on the hip, neatly tucked away fine by Porterfield to get him and Ireland up and running
that's a better delivery, on off stump and seaming away as Porterfield just about pulls his bat inside the line at the last moment
more movement, a fuller length and it jags away off the seam as Porterfield prods without much footwork
now he's lulled into a drive outside off, was actually quite wide, the ball scoots past the outside edge
good line, on off stump, going across the left hander and then just offers to nip back...Porterfield leaves on length as much as line
starts back of a length, decent pace, Stirling defends it to the leg side with a closed face

oh my goodness, that's gone horribly wrong, not sure whether it slipped out or not but it's gone miles down the leg side (think Harmison at his worst) and Buttler can't stop the boundary despite getting a glove to it
now this is short and wide outside off, hammered off the back foot with some fierce power but picks out mid-off
gets on a fuller length outside off, Stirling restrains himself and leaves it alone
short of a length outside off, dropped square into the off side and it's a well-judged single...important to rotate the strike, especially with right and left-handers in
can't adjust his line straight away, on leg stump and Porterfield clips it away to fine leg for his second boundary
gets it on off stump, full length, driven firmly to mid-off
full at off stump, jabbed firmly towards mid-off...Stirling isn't one for much footwork
shorter delivery, quite tight to the body but he's able to cut it down to third man
good delivery, on off stump with a hint of movement, takes the outside and runs wide of the two slips down to third man
defended firmly to the off side
another punchy drive to mid-off as Finn pitches this fuller at the stumps
goes for the pull, wasn't quite as short as he thought, gets taken high on the back leg and the ball runs wide of second slip
fantastic shot, stand-and-deliver from Rankin as he drives firmly through the line of a full delivery and dispatches this past cover
same again, perhaps even better this time, full outside off and Stirling pings it through the off side with a beautifully clean strike
drags the length back and gets it on off stump, defended towards square leg
this zings off the middle of the bat again, but goes straight to Taylor at cover

gone! Rankin has his first England ODI wicket. Back of a length at off stump, squares up Stirling with a touch of seam movement, takes a thick edge high on the bat and carries low to second slip where Ballance held a sharp chance
nearly has a fiddle at this outside off, but think he left it alone at the last minute, short of a length and climbs through to Buttler
short of a length at off stump, defended into the covers
gets too full this time, Porterfield leans into a compact cover drive which races over a quick outfield
not so full this time, outside off, left alone
pushed across outside off, shoulders arms again
gets across his stumps and defends this back towards Finn
offers up width which allows Porterfield to free his arms with a strong square drive wide of point
back of a length on middle and off, defended to the off side
wider outside off, Joyce leaves it well alone
short and down the leg side, not a million miles from leg stump but still a wide
full at off stump, pushed back down the pitch where Rankin makes the long reach down
takes the pad into the leg side, Taylor can't stop the single from square leg
worked to square leg
that's loose outside off, aims an expansive drive to a ball that wasn't that full and is fortunate not to edge to the keeper
short of a length, Joyce is behind the line and defends
touch of extra bounce this time, but Joyce plays it well as he tucks it behind square on the leg side
on off stump, defended back where it came from
that's a good delivery, moves away off the seam from around off stump and beats Porterfield's outside edge
this causes a few problems, short of a length and nips back at Porterfield who tries to drop his hands and gets taken on the arm with the ball bobbling towards the keeper
a little shorter and wider, driven firmly off the back foot but cover makes a good stop
this delivery stops a little in the pitch, it's short of a length, and Joyce is a fraction early on his back-foot punch
hops into line and works this one to square leg

punched into the off side, what's happened here? A bail has fallen off. Rankin is pointing at it. Has it blown off? Or has Joyce touched his stumps? Umpires having a quick look at the TV. Looks like he's hit wicket! His heel just rocked the base of leg stump. Umpires still checking. No real signals given, but Joyce is now walking off. What a way to go. All rather subdued. Not sure the crowd have been given any information. Complete silence.
angled across outside off, left alone
almost pops a return catch here as he defends a fraction early to another delivery that doesn't hurry off the pitch
good line outside off, this one climbs (albeit quite slowly) through to Buttler
outside off, Porterfield just pulls his bat inside the line
short of a length at off stump, defended with an angled bat towards backward point
outside off, left alone
that's well bowled, pitches it fuller and draws Porterfield forward but he doesn't get a massive stride in and is beaten playing away from his body
tries to cut this but it doesn't quite bounce as much as he expected, gets a bottom edge that dribbles back towards Buttler
takes a blow! He's ducked straight into a short ball. It wasn't that short and certainly didn't bounce much. Struck him flush on the side of the helmet not much above stump height
this one does bounce, tennis-ball like, and beats O'Briens attempt to pull it away...flies over the top edge
stands tall and punches this off the back foot to point
beats the outside edge, back of a length and seams away as O'Brien pushes at it off the back foot
pulls again, and picks this up quite cleanly but it wasn't that far from square leg...a clean strike, it would have been a great catch from Taylor
keeps it short of a length, defended on his toes to the off side
excellent diving save a cover by Wright, cuts off another boundary as O'Brien drives this off the back foot
starts down the leg side
full on off stump, Porterfield hangs back and dabs from off stump towards poin
good length on off, Porterfield is forward and getting an inside edge into his front pad which runs up on the on side
touch shorter and punched off the back foot, gets it backward of point and it's well timed so evades James Taylor running round from deep point
fuller length, forward and pushed to backward point
a little short again and punched firmly, this time straight to the deep point Taylor
full and angled in from around the wicket now, blocked from the crease around off off stump
starts by overstepping, blocked just outside off stump
Porterfield clears the front leg and tries to send a length ball over the leg side, misses and gets struck on the pad
full length just wide of off stump, driven at and missed
full length on leg stump, clipped nicely through midwicket, Taylor at deep square leg scurries to his left and saves well, that raced away this outfield is like grease lightning
full on off stump, pushed up towards extra cover
good length around off stump, blocked from the crease towards point
full length and  hint of width enables Porterfield to slash at it and get it out to deep point
a little straight and flicked with the angle down to long leg
touch straight again and whipped down to long leg again
forward and pressed outside off into point
touch overpitched and very nicely driven, handsome stroke, timing was superb and guided it past extra cover, shot of the day
better length and just pushed from an inch outside off into point
another handsome drive, this to the right of extra cover and it races away and beats the sweeper, superb timing
full and wide, driven at and missed
blocked around off stump into the covers
straighter line, dabbed up on the on side, they take a sharp single which is well-judged
full just outside off, driven firmly, well-timed but only to mid-off, settling in well here Porterfield
wide delivery, slashed hard at and it's in the air for a long time but not carrying out to Finn at deep point
full on the stumps, Porterfield nearly caught out by not really moving his feet, drops the bat onto it and gets it away on the on side
floated up from around the wicket, driven steadily out to deep cover
straight line, forward on off stump to push back to the bowler
goes for the reverse sweep from off stump and nails it past point, lovely timing again, where has this timing been all summer?
nicely floated up, Porterfield drawn forward and gets beaten by some nice turn away from the bat
forward, played more carefully here and guided towards point
touch straighter line and worked against the spin towards mid-on
short ball, pulled off the stumps and gets it down to long leg
full delivery on off stump, played forward and pushed up towards cover
slightly shorter length and a hint of width allows Porterfield to punch out to deep cover
full length just outside off, dug out into the gap at cover and they take an easy single
full toss on leg stump, attempted slower ball, clipped out to deep square leg
length ball on off stump, played forward and guided down to third man
floated up on the stumps, O'Brien stays leg side of it and pushes into the covers
floated up and there's turn away that beats the bat, nicely bowled
swept carefully off the stump to deep square leg
nicely bowled again, beating the outside edge, guile and flight, lovely to watch
floated up again, rolled to point from off stump
carefully swept again, a bit of a top-edge but safely out to deep square for a single

pulled from just outside off, totally mistimed, the length wasn't there at all for a pull, cloths it towards mid-on, it doesn't carry, the non-striker gets back but Bopara shies at the stumps, hits them and they run on the ricochet
forward and pressed towards point from just outside off, a sharp single is taken
tighter line and blocked up the wicket
pulled off the stumps down to long leg
full length on off stump, dug out up towards mid-off
touch fuller and driven firmly from off stump to the left of mid-off who is able to scamper across and save the single
lovely delivery and this turns past the outside edge again

swept off the stumps, another top edge, this will carry into the deep, Carberry comes in and oh my goodness drops the catch! That is an absolute stinker, as simple as they come, he made the ground easily and then let it bounce out of his hands at chest height
forward and dropped wide of mid-off for a single
played forward and blocked up the wicket from the stumps
hint of a short length and O'Brien is back to cut but only finds backward point
slightly wide of off stump and left alone
full just outside off, driven through point and they get an easy single to the sweeper
full and wide of off stump, driven out to the sweeper again
touch straighter but still a driveable length, opens the face to find the sweeper once more
guided off the back foot down towards third man, here's Carberry again, and he fumbles again! The crowd cheer but it didn't cost an extra run
full on leg stump and clipped fine for four runs, poor delivery
back on it, length on off stump, dabbed into the covers and extra-cover rushes in to field
touch short, back and clipped wide of mid-on for a single

forward and the turn produces a thin edge that is out of the reach of Buttler, it runs away down towards fine third man, Ballance gives chase, slides and flicks but totally messes it up and it runs into the rope
forward and pressed into the covers from just outside off stump
forward again, this to a fuller ball, pressed back to the bowler
beautiful, turn from off the stumps, past the outside edge and narrowly beats the off stump

quicker ball, slides past the attempted defensive stroke off the back foot and takes the off stump and Tredwell has a much-deserved wicket. He's bowled with lovely flight and generated good turn, should have had a catch in the deep but now deceives O'Brien with a quicker delivery that skidded on; arm ball does the trick
around the wicket, touch short and pulled hard past mid-on, gets it away well enough and that's fifty for Porterfield, a real rarity for him this season
back over the wicket, full on off stump, blocked with bat and pad together
similar area, blocked forward again
touch wider, slashes out to the sweeper and that brings the hundred up at a fairly healthy lick
leg stump line, flicked down to long leg, Carberry yet again...hurrah! Fields with no drama this time
too wide and an easy square drive to the off side sweeper
length ball played off the back foot to extra-cover
floated up again and again beats the outside edge, lovely stuff
back to cut and misses outside off
sharp turn this time from a wide line so it was well away from Porterfield's block
straight and fuller, smothered coming forward
full length wide of off stump, well forward and blocked through point
poor line and it runs off the pads down to fine leg, Rankin can't save it from long leg
length ball, hint of shape back into the left-hander, Porterfield angles it to point from the crease
length ball a foot wide of off stump, angled away again but again can't beat point
fuller delivery, driven out wide of the sweeper so they get two
forward on off stump and pressed to the off side sweeper once more
forward on the stumps and dabbed up on the off side
floated up outside off, Porterfield plays inside the line
straight line, blocked up the wicket coming forward
bit of a slash outside off aiming across the line, big edge could have gone anywhere but it's into the gap behind point
swept off the stumps out to deep square leg
touch short and clipped out to deep square leg
floated up on off stump, driven firmly into the off side, wide of mid-off for a single
slightly back in length, tucked from the stumps into the off side
slightly wide of off stump, flicked at and gets a thick outside edge that runs down to third man
better line, tucked from off stump to midwicket
straight line again, worked to midwicket again hanging back
brings him forward this time and finds midwicket again with a flick off the stumps
driven from just outside off, a thick outside edge runs down to third man
floated up, big stride in just outside off and a firm drive down to long-off

floated up on off stump, turns back and strikes the batsman on the front pad, did he get outside the line, no, he's been given out the turn has convinced the umpire that came back enough, probably going on to hit the stumps but Wilson may feel he got outside the line, it was certainly very close. Well bowled from Tredwell though, nicely floated up again and finds more turn
floated up wide of off stump, firmly driven and gets a thick outside edge to deep point
quicker delivery, Porterfield caught on the crease and gets beaten outside off, yet again
forward just on off, don't play across the line Will, bit of a leading edge there back up the wicket
forward on off stump, angled towards point
pushed off the back foot from just outside off and he was very hurried and got a thick inside edge towards square leg, Porterfield called him through for a quick single
good length on the stumps, blocked in the crease
forward just outside off to a length ball, angles this towards point
fuller ball, pressed up towards mid-off from off stump
finds mid-off again, this time with a front-foot slap via a few bobbles, that was well saved
length ball slides away from off stump, Porterfield follows it and plays and misses
clipped with the spin in the air from middle and off and narrowly avoids midwicket
full length on middle, driven down to long-off
firm sweep from off stump and well-timed, powers it's way to the square leg fence
flatter quicker ball ran up the wicket, blocking in the crease
floated up a foot outside off, driven firmly to short extra-cover, Carberry again, he's alright now
over the wicket now, floated up just outside off, played forward and ran back to the bowler
short outside off, pulled hard and gets it past mid-on for four, poor start
another short ball, this on the stumps, pulled off a top edge and it runs fine, long leg able to cut it off
slightly back of a length and slapped hard out to the cover sweeper
length ball on middle and leg, turned down to long leg, fine of the fielder
bit of a cutter just outside off, pushed firmly off the back foot and nearly find extra-cover, wide of the sweeper
full on the stumps, rolled back up the wicket coming forward
more spin, beats the outside edge as he stretches forward
swept off the stumps out to deep square-leg
grips from outside off, lobs into the leg side off the pad
goes for the sweep, doesn't make contact, gets taken on the pad but he makes sure it's well outside off stump
edged! But it flies past (almost through) Ballance at slip. Was a cut shot off the back foot, the edge flew quickly and he barely had time to move. He's stood very close.
tucked off the back foot into the leg side
full outside off, defended to the covers
tries to open the face and find a gap backward of point but picks out the fielder
defended carefully to backward point
at cutter from Wright, comes forward and drives, picks out cover...decent over so far
gets this one through, offered a short and wide delivery, O'Brien places it nice between short third-man and backward point...Morgan had just brought third man up
punched down to long-on
full outside off, O'Brien gets to the pitch and bunts it down the ground
tossed up from round the wicket, driven to cover
on middle and off, pushed to the off side
a fraction shorter, Porterfield goes into the back foot and plays to cover
forward this time and again finds cover
floated up a little slower, full on middle, softly defended to the off side and that's Tredwell done
tries to turn this into the leg side, almost gets a leading edge but it runs along the ground to mid-off
this time it is a full leading edge, again working a full ball to leg, but it doesn't carry to cover
worked out to deep midwicket
driven out to deep cover
punched down the ground off the back foot
full on off stump, places this nicely into the deep to the left of deep cover which allows him back for a second
full outside off, hint of shape into the right hander, defended square on the off side
superbly placed...it was basically a long hop from Bopara, but O'Brien made sure he placed it between the deep fielders on the leg side as he split square leg and long leg
better line and length, on off stump, takes a thick outside edge to point
top catch! Bonus for England. Another short delivery but this time O'Brien's pull picks out Morgan at midwicket who takes a sharp diving catch to his right. Then drop-kicks the ball in celebration.
short of a length, Mooney goes across his crease and defends
well, that's given a wide but it almost took out leg stump. Mooney moved right across his crease. As long as the umpire is consistent
defended off the back foot, lobs into the leg side, in the air for a short while, but well short of mid-on
outside off stump, defended back to Finn
very full this time, he can't time his drive and the ball dribbles to mid-off
this time he squeezes it off a thick outside edge to third man
tight on middle and off, no room for Porterfield to free his arms, picks out point as he drives
fuller at off stump, driven sweetly but it goes to cover
this goes in the air for a while as it's punched towards mid-off, but was never really a threat of being a catch...excellent over from Finn
starts with a full toss which is clipped out to deep square-leg
short of a length, comes slowly off the surface and Porterfield mistimes it back to the bowler
manages to force this off the back foot out to deep cover
no footwork from Mooney as he prods outside off stump, well away from his body, and gets beaten...the ball scoots through quite low
full at middle and off, flicked down to long leg
lack of pace in the pitch does for Porterfield again, completely mistimes this drive to a short-of-a-length delivery and can only it flap it back down the pitch
short of a length on the hip, flicked out to deep square-leg and they complete a second but one is called a short run
pushed to backward point...a no-ball from Finn for hitting the non-striker's stumps. So no free hit
tries to place it past backward point but picks out the fielder
short of a length, very tight from Finn, defended back to the bowler
beats an attempted pull, goes underneath the bat
very full outside off, Mooney plays over the top of the ball which runs along the ground out of the footmarks to Buttler
full at middle and off, neatly placed through the leg side wide of long-on who also can't pick the ball up cleanly
touch short outside off, increasingly hard to time shots now, this takes a bottom edge from a cut back to Buttler

another drop by Carberry! He's had a nightmare in the field today. Porterfield picked up a short ball with a pull, but didn't keep it down, Carberry had to make some ground, it was a low catch, but should have been taken
chopped down to third man
now this flies in the air just over backward point as he upper cuts
pulled along the ground this time, Carberry in from deep square leg and just about manages to pick it up cleanly
appeal for lbw, he came right across his stumps aiming to leg and actually got outside off stump
short of a length at leg stump, gets inside the line and flicks down to long leg
short on leg stump again, pulled firmly but straight to long leg
lobs off the pads into the off side, called through for a quick leg-bye
not giving him anything full, this comes down off a bottom edge and runs backwards past the stumps...called through by the non-striker
almost another chop on, trying to glide down to third man but was cramped for room
the first attempt at something verging on a slog, gives himself room to leg and tries to heave over deep midwicket but doesn't make contact
around the wicket, full toss, reverse swept for four, nice strike
gives himself room and slaps this wide of long-off
some turn but it's short and outside off, cut wide of the cover sweeper and they get back for two
another cut, this straight at extra-cover
floated up outside off and hammered wide of long-off, lovely timing
straight line, played with the turn and dabbed into the covers
leg stump delivery, dabbed down to long-on
clears the front leg and slaps a length ball to extra-cover from off stump
clears the front leg and hammers over the leg side, is this all the way? It is! Porterfield has a hundred, what a captain's innings and what a way to bring it up, this sails over midwicket
length ball on the stumps, angled down to third man
forward and gets a thick inside edge off the stumps down to long leg
leg stump and full, goes to flick it to leg and misses
slower ball, blocked forward and tucks it into square leg for a single
forward and dabs this into midwicket for a quick single
across his stumps, goes to flick this to leg and misses, the ball goes over middle stump
step to leg and cuts out to deep cover
forward and blocked off the stumps backward of point for a single
short ball outside off, tried to be swatted down the ground but mistimed it back to the bowler
full ball wide of off stump, driven firmly at, gets it backward of point but third man is able to save the second
just back in length, goes to Dilshan this even though long leg is back, misses but takes a single off the thigh pad to Buttler's left
huge swing a complete miss, wild strike that, but Buttler fumbles it on the bounce and they skate through for a bye
length ball, swung at down the ground and gets it over mid-off for four, good strike
tries to clear the leg side this time and misses completely
fuller ball following Mooney stepping to leg, swings and totally misses again
back of a length on the stumps, swung into the leg side and they get two wide of deep square leg
fuller ball driven out to deep cover
slower short ball, cut at and missed, it bounced short of Buttler and spun away from him, past the pads for four byes
full ball on the stumps, goes to flick to leg, the ball rebounds towards point and they get a single
step to the off side, flicked over short long leg, great shot, good awareness of the field
very full outside off, driven firmly out to deep cover

full and follows Porterfield again, who is stepping to leg this time, he's ended up yorked well outside leg stump and the ball cannons into the stumps. Bit unfortunate for Porterfield but well bowled Rankin, realising the batsman had stepped away and followed him to cramp him up, it was a good full, straight delivery and Porterfield was nowhere near it

ful ball comes off the pad to Buttler's left, he throws at the non-striker's end as they take a leg bye and the ball comes off Johnston and cannons away towards the long-off boundary, Morgan chases and saves what would have been five
goes for the dab sweep outside leg and misses, wide anyway
length ball swung into the off side, just enough bat on it to avoid extra-cover running back
another leg side wide
step to leg and a big swing a miss at a length ball that narrowly evades off stump

full and straight, Mooney misses and is given out lbw it looked very straight that. Good pace from Rankin, the batsman hurried in trying to play to leg and misses, caught very low on the pad in front of middle. Slight question over whether it might have pitched just outside leg but it was so full it's very hard to tell and looked very straight
full wide of off stump, driven off low on the bat to deep cover
length ball that just shapes away a touch , flicked at and missed outside off stump
full ball just outside off, driven towards mid-off, they take on the fielder and get home
goes to pull this and misses, comes off the pad back towards the bowler
full and straight, dug out down the ground, pretty straight, Carberry with the chase round from long-on and can't save the second
step to leg and cracked hard square on the off side for a single to deep cover
full length on off stump, forced into the on side, they get an easy single to midwicket on the edge of the circle
just back in length on off stump, a big swing over the leg side and this is nailed into the crowd, lovely strike
full and straight, strikes the pad, probably going down, it runs towards third man for a leg bye
full at leg stump, tried to be swung down the ground but got an inside edge into the pad that runs to cover for a single
length ball just outside off, big heave across the line, misses completely
length ball just outside off, cut into the covers for a single but Finn has knocked down the stumps again with his knee
step to leg and a swing from outside off on the bounce to mid-off, good save on the bounce that, it was awkward
fuller on the stumps, aimed to leg, comes off the pad towards point
short ball and a poor line with long leg up in the circle, helped on it's way to the fence, poor bowling
short ball pulled again, this time both men are back on the leg side fence, deep square leg fields
length ball at the stumps, Johnston gives himself room and dabs wide of backward point for a single
full on off stump, clothed to mid-on, they refuse the run but Carberry fumbles it anyway! What a stinker he is having today
slower ball bouncer, batsman through with the shot several days too soon, hits him on the back and it runs towards point
another slower ball, swing and a miss outside off, Buttler is again unable to field on the bounce and they get a bye on the rebound to long leg
back of a length pulled down to Carberry at deep backward square, it's bobbling a little but Carberry saves well
step to leg and a big inside edge through square leg gives them a single
full slower ball outside off, swung at and missed and hallelujah Buttler has stopped one
full ball on the stumps and a big swing into the leg side, connects well and there's enough bat on it to clear cow corner, good thump
goes again, this from a short ball, doesn't quite nail it and finds deep square leg on the bounce
full length at leg stump, Sorensen steps away and hammers it down the ground, what a stroke, timing was superb and a great way to end the innings

inn2.comm: pitched up wide of the off stump, Carberry watches it through to the keeper
length ball, angled across the left-hander from over the wicket, opens the face and steers one into the gully
length delivery, holding its line on off stump, Wright covers up in defence
goes across his stumps and defends the ball softly into the covers
this nearly does Wright a mischief, pitching and seaming back at the batsman, maybe stays a touch low too and he does well to get his bat down
bounces off a length and Wright defends square on the back foot
full and sliding down the leg side, just a tickle of bat on it but the ball races fine for a first boundary, for England and Carberry
better line, Carberry stays back and gets behind a length ball
angled across and left alone outside off
good ball, nibbles away from Carberry off a length and zips past the outside edge
length delivery on the stumps, Carberry taps into the leg side from the crease
drops back and steers a length ball down into the ground behind point
Murtagh maintains a disciplined line in the channel outside off, Wright lunges forward to defend
straighter, goes across and works a fullish ball to leg, midwicket fields but they pick up one
touch shorter, on the stumps, nudged to square leg

an appeal ripples round the ground, taken up by the crowd even as it died in Murtagh's throat... Carberry played back and got an inside edge on to his pads, hit him outside the line of off, too, on its way across the left-hander
drops short and scooped over square leg, Carberry leaning back on a solid base and helping the ball to the boundary
another lbw appeal, must have been a bit of bat involved, though, as a run is signalled, a full ball striking Carberry in front of leg and rolling away

pitched up and swinging in, hit in front again - and that's out! Carberry manages just 10 runs in atonement for his two drops (plus 0-12 with the ball) and his ODI debut is ended by a man who has played 66 of them with distinction for Ireland. Johnston got the right line to a left-hander, the ball pitching on middle, holding its line and would have lopped the top of the pole
shapes back in from outside off, Taylor gets his bat down to block
gets forward and defends into the off side
touch short, holding its line around off stump, defended playing back
fullish and angling in on middle and off stump, Taylor works it off his pads through midwicket for a scampered single to get off the mark
tight lines from Wollongong's favourite son, Wright presses forward to block
length delivery, Taylor takes the bottom hand off the bat as he jabs it to leg for a single
gets across and plays the ball straight back down the track
touch short though it doesn't get up and Wright has to stick his bum right out to swivel through a pull shot, played it well and the ball flew flat to deep square leg for his first boundary
drops the ball towards point, thinks about one but the fielder hares in
drops short, Wright squares up and taps short of midwicket
gets across his stumps and defends a length ball
outside off, Taylor gets in line and blocks
fires a length ball down the leg side, Taylor flicks and misses and there's a muted appeal from O'Brien - called wide
turned off the stumps towards midwicket
good length, over the top of off stump, Taylor punches back down the track
that's a little gem from Johnston, full and enticing, drawing Taylor into a drive as the ball pitches and straightens past the outside edge
extravagant movement but the ball seams wide of the tramlines outside off
little bit of extra bounce off a length, hits near the splice of the bat as Taylor pushes away from his body
good length in the channel, pushes into the covers - tight stuff from Johnston, who has 1 for 7 from his three overs
defends a shortish ball from the crease
gets forward, pushing at a length ball that seams back, clips the inside edge - Murtagh's appeal turned down

hit in front again, umpire Mark Hawthorne shakes his head, deciding Wright had got outside the line of off ... but Hawk-Eye shows he hadn't, the ball would have clattered into middle and leg halfway up
lunges forward again and gets bat on ball in defence this time
tries to pull to leg but doesn't connect properly
comes forward and dabs into the off side, can't get it through - that's a maiden
another pearler from Johnston, seaming and bouncing past Taylor's outside edge as he comes forwards
comes forward and pushes a length ball into the off side
hops back and nudges the ball into a gap square on the leg side, they run hard and Taylor picks up two
stays back and pushes square with an open bat face
lovely stroke, Taylor springs forward to an overpitched delivery and pierces the field through extra cover, well timed and it races to the fence
better length, on middle and off stump, tapped into the leg side
Wright gets a stride in, opens the face and guides a length ball to backward point

stays back and attempts to run the ball to third man - but Wright has played on! The slowness of the pitch did for him, cross-batted shots always dangerous in these circumstances and a thick bottom edge sent the ball straight down on to the base of off stump. Wright's head sags in unison, he kicks the turf - Ireland are right on top here
fullish, outside off, leans into a forward defensive

tries to leave, doesn't withdraw the bat quickly enough and there's a feather on it - Ballance is gone, caught behind! Indecision from Ballance, facing only his second ball, he wanted to leave but his muscles took a moment to catch up with his brain and the ball brushed the face on its way through
pitched up outside off, steps out to defend on the front foot
stays in the crease and pats the ball towards point - huge over, a double-wicket maiden from Murtagh
walks across his stumps and nudges a half-volley towards mid-on
another menacing cheer ripples around the ground as Taylor plays and misses outside off, the sound of bat on ground hinting at an edge that wasn't
stays back and blocks a shortish delivery
back of a length, defended on the back foot in front of the stumps
skips forward and prods the ball fine of mid-on, sets off for a very tight single and makes it, although the shy at the bowler's end missed anyway
goes back and squirts one off the hips behind square, they hustle another quick single
angled across outside off, Morgan covers the line and defends
hops back and squeezes the ball out on the leg side, briefly in the air but drops safe
edged but it flies past the diving man in the gully, little bit of luck for Morgan, who gave Murtagh the charge and then played a nothing dab at a length ball, got squared up as it left him slightly
goes deep in the crease, cuts straight to backward point
bit of width, Taylor stays low (not too difficult for him) and chops a late cut down to third man
length ball on the stumps, Murtagh comes forward and shows it a straight bat
on the stumps, clipped through backward square for a single
touch short and angled across outside off, Morgan steers the ball to the sweeper out through point
goes across and whips another one through square leg
on the legs, flicked off the pads by Morgan for another comfortable single
drops short, defended back down the track
touch short, sliding towards leg stump and again easily picked off for a single through square
opens the face and steers the ball straight to backward point
slightly full, on middle stump, Taylor plays across his front pad and clips to midwicket
comes forward, punches a fullish ball to mid-on
waits on a full ball and then spanks a cover drive for four, nicely done, a really wristy, punchy strike with a high follow through
gets on the front foot and pushes into the covers
length ball, played on the up back down the ground, sweetly struck but straight into the stumps at the non-striker's end
drags his length down, Morgan tucks the ball off his hips through square and the fielder runs in off the boundary to keep them to one
big lbw appeal from Sorensen, as Taylor stayed back and was hit on the knee, think there was an inside edge, though, might have been heading past leg
short and wide, Taylor throws the hands through a vigorous cut stroke, just gets one to third man
pulled flat and hard through square, again picks out the fielder
back of a length, Taylor gets on top of it and pings a drive in front of square, well placed between the point and cover fielders
length delivery, better line around off stump, defended coming forwards

draws Taylor forward, he pushes and gets an edge past the keeper, probably would have dropped short of first slip, had there been one in, instead went between Wilson and the man at third-slip-cum-gully
pitched up outside off, comes forward and pushed back to the bowler
shortish and blocked from in front of the stumps
plays with a slightly closed face towards mid-on, no run there

skids on, through the defences and bowled him! Murtagh has a third, England's little man defeated by one that came back at him - though in truth it was a loose shot, left a gap between bat and pad and Murtagh located it
length delivery outside the line of off, gets forward and shows it the face of the bat in defence
goes round the wicket to the left-handed Morgan, who drops back and dabs one through point
good length in the channel outside off stump, left alone
short and wide and Bopara threads a delicate cut shot through square on the off side for three
length ball, in the corridor, blocked on the front foot towards cover
leans out and drives on the up, finds a gap in the covers and they get a couple more to the cause
short and angled down the leg side, Morgan attempts to flick off his hips and the ball rolls away via the protective padding
slightly leg side, flicked down towards fine leg
gets forward and works a length ball towards midwicket
nicely timed from Bopara, bit of width to work with and he frees up the arms to caress a late cut through point
length on off stump, leans out and defends
that's a terrific shot from Bopara, little bit of width, little bit short and thrashed through the covers off the back foot
on the stumps, tighter line and turned defensively to leg
floated up outside off, punched firmly down to long-on
goes to dab sweep and misses around leg stump
forward just outside off to block up the wicket
floated up on the stumps, ran up to the right of the bowler
leg stump and swept, only as far as short long leg
forward on the stumps, dabbed into midwicket but the bowler is out quickly to field
full on leg stump, clipped into the on side in the air, not a millions miles away from the bowler's left hand
full just outside off stump, pushed forward back to the bowler
length ball on the stumps, worked away from the crease via square leg into the deep for a single
forward on off stump, blocked off the inner half of the bat towards midwicket
length ball a foot outside off stump, Bopara hangs back and guides it down to third man
firm drive back towards the bowler and the stumps to the fielding
forward and pushed up on the off side from off stump
overpitched and driven down to long-off
flicked from a foot outside off with the spin down to long-on
full on the stumps, tucked wide of mid-on for an easy single
full outside off, reverse swept but only finds short third man who makes a good save
swept the other way this time and here there's no short fielder in the way, single to deep square
around the wicket, a floaty full toss, pushes firmly down to long-off
back of a length outside off, cut firmly and Dockrell saves well to his right at cover
good length on off stump and Bopara unsure in coming forward, thick outside edge down to third man
superb drive, great timing, slightly overpitched delivery and Morgan eases it away past extra cover, it races to the rope, glorious
same line, better length, Morgan forward to push into the covers
full on middle and leg, forward and pressed into midwicket
forward just outside off to press out to deep cover
swept hard from just outside off and Morgan collects another boundary with another superbly timed stroke
step across off stump and tickled with the turn to midwicket
touch shorter outside off, back and moved with the turn for a single backward of square
forward on off stump, dabbed towards point and they jump away for a sharp single
back and tucked to leg but too close to short midwicket for a single
touch short, pulled hard from just outside off, finds deep square leg on the bounce
square slash from outside off to point, timed it superbly again
full toss outside off, driven but finds point again, should have been two boundaries
outside off again, cut again, this more delicately and finds short third man, still run through for a single
tight off stump line, guided down to third man
this time Morgan does send O'Brien to the fence, short on off stump and Morgan plays with the angle from around the wicket and finds the deep backward square fence
floated up outside off, driven firmly to deep cover
full toss on off stump, clipped wide of mid-on's dive and they get back for the second
full toss down leg, would have been wide, Morgan swept it straight to short long leg, lucky for the bowler
forward and blocked up the wicket from middle stump
reverse swept from middle stump, bit airy but gets it out to deep point and the fielder slides and makes a superb save
firm drive down to long-off from the stumps
delicate paddle sweep from just outside off, nicely played and gets it fine enough of deep backward square for three
swept from middle and leg, finds short long leg
back in the crease, cutting hard out to deep cover, there's a fumble but they refuse the second
mistimed drive from outside off to extra cover
swept off the stumps to deep backward square
full on leg stump, clipped straight to midwicket
forward just outside off, dabbing towards backward point
touch short and able to cut this past extra-cover, long-off does exceptionally well to dive and save four
leg stump and yorker length, dug out into a vacant midwicket and they take a single
tossed up too much and Bopara drives it firmly past past mid-off, great timing and picks up another useful boundary
horrible full toss outside off stump, slapped wide of the cover sweeper for two
pushed in the same direction, this time deep cover is across to save the second
played off the back foot towards the bowler
tossed up outside off and slapped over midwicket's head for four, fetched it from outside off, bit of a swipe and gets four
plays this in-to-out but drives too much out and finds deep cover just for a single
tossed up outside off, worked with the spin towards midwicket
touch flatter and straighter, clipped towards the same fielder
goes for the sweep and nails it, right off the meat of the bat and gets it backward of square for a one bounce four
around the wicket, tickling fine behind square on the leg side, short long leg can't save the single
forward just outside off to dab towards point
short and cut hard, only as far as short extra-cover
back and cuts again, this probably too full to cut, gets it off an under edge into the covers
forward to block on the stumps
back and this time the cut evades the in-field and they get two wide of deep cover
forward on the stumps, blocking up into the covers
waits for this a little more in the crease, dabs more square on the off side and they can take the single here
rather slogged down the ground from outside off stump, heart in the mouth moment for Morgan but well short of long-on in the end
short and whipped to leg, midwicket makes a lovely save, could have been four that
finds extra-cover this time with a well-timed back foot punch
forward on off stump and dabbed into the covers, up comes Wilson from behind the stumps to save the run
goes to pull this and Morgan gets a toe end towards point, through too early there
full toss on leg stump, clipped down to deep backward square leg only, few boundary chances being missed
Bopara finds midwicket again with a flick off the front foot
now evades the fielder at midwicket and gets it wide of long-on, just a single though despite a single
nice delivery, turn away from the off stump and Morgan was poking at it and got beaten
flat delivery on off stump, pushed out to deep cover and fifty for Morgan, a lovely innings, now can he do a Porterfield, England need him, that's Morgan's first ODI fifty since August last year
down the track, picks it up into the on side and clears long-on, reached for it but timed it well into the stands
paddle swept from outside off, Wilson saw it early and anticipated the stroke, dived but it was just out of reach, runs towards fine leg
full and clipped with the turn down to long-on
Bopara back and cutting square on the off side for a single to the sweeper
full ball wide of off, Morgan tries to cut and misses
flatter and quicker on leg stump, tickled around the corner for a single
very full on the stumps, punched up the wicket to the bowler
back and cut wide of the cover sweeper, they run hard and get two
full just outside off, driven firmly down to long-off
down the track and a huge strike out of the ground over midwicket, that was absolutely nailed, right out of the screws and brings up the hundred partnership at a run-a-ball, top effort from these two
down the track again and another big strike, this over long-on, sails for six again, great timing
over the wicket now, flat and length on middle, tapped to midwicket
full outside off, driven out to deep cover, wasn't perfectly timed, the fielder had a lot to do anyway but the fumble made the second easy
short and pulled around the corner for four, awful delivery, easily put away
full toss outside off, driven to extra-cover who can only parry and they sprint back for the second
short again and pulled out wide of deep midwicket for another couple
full on the stumps, steadily rolled down the ground, very straight and they get two more
driven at outside off, a thick outside edge finds short third man
length ball dabbed towards point from off stump, Wilson pops up to field
swept from leg stump, short long leg goes to his left and saves the second
slightly back of a length and clipped through square leg
back and cut hard down to long-off, fifty for Bopara, played really nicely here, calm and collected
back foot push up the wicket, Dockrell goes to his left to field
paddle swept from outside off, it runs fine for a couple
wide on the crease, angled into off stump, Bopara forward to block up the wicket
wide angle again, back foot push down the ground and midwicket comes across to save really well with a dive
full delivery, firm chip down the ground one bounce well in front of long-on
chopped hanging back from outside off, finds third man
low full toss, driven wide of deep cover and they get a couple
full delivery, driven steadily down the ground, long-on in quickly and saves the second
length ball outside off stump, played back and fielded by Johnston in his follow through
goes back and steers a length delivery through point
length delivery pushed through outside off, gentle pace and Bopara opens the face of his bat to run one down to third man
tight on the stumps, slightly back of a length and defended into the off side
big ole swing of the arms from Morgan, think he was aiming down the ground but it squirted away off the toe of the bat past Stirling's dive at backward point and down to third man for a couple
on a length, angled across, drops back and glides another single off the bat face to third man
fullish and wide of the stumps, Morgan tries to drag to leg, it bobbles just off the cut strip
pitched up outside off again, gets under this and slices it high over backward point, there's not a man out there and the ball runs away
comes forward, pushes a length ball towards mid-off
stands tall and steers a length ball through point, Morgan wants a couple but there's no wriggle room there

Bopara is seeing the ball big today, might as well be that beach ball we saw in the crowd earlier - Mooney went over the wicket, sent down a length delivery, which R-Bop creamed over wide long-on with a free swing of the bat
touch shorter, on the stumps and worked to midwicket, who stops it smartly
round the wicket to Morgan, not all that full but Morgan is confident in hitting through the line, clobbering the ball for a one-bounce four over cover
length ball sliding down the leg side, nudged behind square and they squirrel away one more as the throw comes in
back over the wicket, full and wide and steered to backward point with an angled bat
gets forward and punches a single down the ground to long-off - that's the 150 partnership between these two
cuts hard, gets a thick top edge, Morgan not entirely in control of the shot but it's wide of the third man, Dockrell, who runs round and does well to cut it off before running out of play

pitched up in the slot and scalped over extra cover, right out of the middle and it flies for six - that's a pretty emphatic way to go to your hundred! That's Morgan's first ODI ton since Pakistan at Southampton in 2010
this stops in the pitch a little and Bopara gets under it, plays the sand wedge towards midwicket but there's no one there and it lands safely
on the stumps, taps the ball back on the on side
leans forward and drills the ball towards mid-off
steps away early and gives himself room to laser a precision drive through the covers, that'll do, pet
veers down the leg side and Bopara uses the pace to pick up another boundary, sweeping the ball to deep backward square
backs away early again, O'Brien this time fires the ball down full and wide of off - Bopara nowhere near it but that's his own fault
drops short, bit of a half-tracker and Morgan pulls forcefully across the line to send the ball zipping to the rope - four more
tossed up, outside off and misses trying to sweep this time
short and outside off, attempts a reverse-handed swat and fails to connect again
flatter, maybe a touch short, Morgan skips forward and pushes to long-on
pushed through very quickly on the stumps, drops back and punches into the covers
floated up, much more air, down the leg side, though
little bit short, goes back and pierces the off-side field for one into the deep
sixer! Bopara has hit this like Jack Nicklaus on the 18th tee, picking up a full-length ball and pulling it high over deep midwicket for another huge maximum
brutal, straight back down the ground this time, high follow through and the ball explodes off the face of the bat for another boundary
slower-ball bouncer, I think, Bopara didn't quite pick it but neither did Wilson and it runs away for extras
pitched up outside off, pushed to mid-off and they race through for a single
excellent pick up, spots the slower ball on a length outside off and belabours it over midwicket for another six
opens the face and steers one more through point
length ball, stays back and pulls flat through midwicket to the sweeper
steps away, Sorensen follows him and Bopara lofts uppishly down the ground for a single to long-on
angled across, tapped back to the bowler
steps out and pushes a length ball into the covers
leaves his crease and hacks across the line, gets one through midwicket
this comes out wrong, low full toss on leg stump and Bopara wristily flicks the ball to the rope at deep backward square leg
attempts to clear the ropes again, slogging a full ball towards deep square leg, doesn't have the legs though and Niall O'Brien settles underneath it only to drop the chance. Oh dear
little bit short, on leg stump and heaved over midwicket, there's no one out there and Bopara is into the nineties
smashed back down the ground, right out of the screws and the ball disappears flat over long-on for the eighth six of the England innings, all scored by these two!
makes room and drills the ball over extra cover, another meaty connection and the ball bounces to the rope - that's Ravi Bopara's century, his first in one-day internationals
full toss, sweeps through backward square, picks out and man and that will just be a single
and there it is, Dockrell is launched over the deep midwicket fence again, Morgan capping a superb fightback to secure England's six-wicket win with yet another six!
